import{_ as e,c as a,o as r,ae as o}from"./chunks/framework.Bi6zybwU.js";const c=JSON.parse('{"title":"Preparations","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"preparations.md","filePath":"preparations.md"}'),l={name:"preparations.md"};function i(n,t,s,d,h,u){return r(),a("div",null,[...t[0]||(t[0]=[o('<h1 id="preparations" tabindex="-1">Preparations <a class="header-anchor" href="#preparations" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Preparations&quot;">​</a></h1><p>In order to install Linux on your PS4, we need some things:</p><ol><li>A compatible, moddable PS4 (newest exploit is the BD-JB by Gezine, <a href="https://github.com/Gezine/BD-JB-1250" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">available here</a>) <ol><li>You need to know your PS4 Southbridge. To check that, after loading GoldHen, go into Settings &gt; System &gt; System Information and note the name. It can be: <ol><li>Aeolia (PS4 Phat)</li><li>Belize/Belize2 or some other variant of this (Slim and Pro)</li><li>Baikal (Newer Silms and Pros) <ol><li>Baikal systems can&#39;t install Linux on the internal HDD (more on that later)</li></ol></li></ol></li></ol></li><li>The Linux files (downloads are further into the guide) <ol><li>bzImage (the kernel)</li><li>initramfs.cpio.gz (Linux loader)</li><li>A distro of your choice, already preinstalled and modified to work on the PS4 <ol><li>You can also make your own. More on that later.</li></ol></li></ol></li><li>A device to install Linux to, either: <ol><li>Internal HDD (Baikal still unsupported, veeery slow)</li><li>External HDD/SSD</li></ol></li><li>A lot of patience and time!</li></ol><h1 id="getting-the-required-files" tabindex="-1">Getting the required files <a class="header-anchor" href="#getting-the-required-files" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Getting the required files&quot;">​</a></h1><p>Because getting this files is a complete and utter joke, I&#39;ve decided that reuploading them myself is probably the better idea. I&#39;ll be reuploading this stuff on this GitHub. Again do not send a cease and desist letter to my house like the Maryo company.</p><h2 id="kernel" tabindex="-1">Kernel <a class="header-anchor" href="#kernel" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Kernel&quot;">​</a></h2><p>Let&#39;s start with the kernels: they are very important as they have the software that controls all of the PS4&#39;s hardware. There&#39;s plenty of them, and I&#39;ll list them from newer to older:</p><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>Kernel</th><th>Source code</th><th>Developer</th><th>Extra info</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>6.15</td><td><a href="https://github.com/crashniels/linux" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a></td><td>crashniels</td><td>No precompiled downloads available</td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://github.com/DionKill/ps4-linux-tutorial/blob/main/PS4%20Linux/kernels/5.15.25-rc1_belize_ThinLTO_Led_LAVANDE_Debian-Trixie_LLVM_19.1.2.zip" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">5.15.25-rc1</a></td><td>N/A, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mpcE9LLS59k" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">original link</a></td><td>saya</td><td>Necessary for CachyOS. Multiple power LED colors supported. LTO. Includes the bootargs.txt.</td></tr><tr><td>5.15.15</td><td>N/A, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mpcE9LLS59k" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">original link</a></td><td>saya</td><td>Multiple power LED colors supported. LTO.</td></tr><tr><td>Other</td><td>Maybe</td><td>Plenty</td><td>I&#39;m too bored to add more.<br><a href="https://ps4linux.com/downloads/#PS4_Linux_Kernel_Downloads" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">For now, check this.</a></td></tr></tbody></table><div class="note custom-block github-alert"><p class="custom-block-title">NOTE</p><p>If you are having issues, you could try a different kernel, though remember that the older the version and the less compatibility there is with newer programs and games.</p></div><h2 id="initramfs" tabindex="-1">Initramfs <a class="header-anchor" href="#initramfs" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Initramfs&quot;">​</a></h2><p>This is the rescue shell that boots your Linux installer/installation. I&#39;ll be using one only, and it&#39;s going to be the one that was originally created for PSXITARCH, a distro based on Arch made by the PS3ITA Forums. <a href="https://github.com/DionKill/ps4-linux-tutorial/blob/main/PS4%20Linux/initramfs.zip" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Here it is</a>.</p><h2 id="distros-that-you-actually-wanna-use" tabindex="-1">Distros (that you ACTUALLY wanna use) <a class="header-anchor" href="#distros-that-you-actually-wanna-use" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Distros (that you ACTUALLY wanna use)&quot;">​</a></h2><p>Yes! Finally the time has come. Which one will you choose? Honestly there&#39;s a neptillion distros. Most however, are very outdated, especially the ones on the PS4Linux&#39;s website list. So here I&#39;m listing the ones that are actually new and I&#39;d recommend you install:</p><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>Distro</th><th>Base</th><th>Developer</th><th>Info</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href="https://ps4linux.com/forums/d/347-linux-pack-cachyos-final-fix-biglinux-and-other-fix" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">CachyOS</a></td><td>Arch</td><td><a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCU-eXjZ7Ud0k2wC_14mqdOw" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Elokuba (Qba)</a></td><td>&quot;Final Fix&quot;. The distro is half polish, half english. But it works and is up to date. Uses KDE.</td></tr><tr><td>CachyOS</td><td>Arch</td><td><a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCU-eXjZ7Ud0k2wC_14mqdOw" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Elokuba (Qba)</a>, DionKill</td><td>My version. It fixes language (mostly) and removes the anime girl backgrounds that I found particularly annoying to have on the living room TV (with other people).</td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://ps4linux.com/forums/d/342-manjaro-from-scratch" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Manjaro</a></td><td>Arch</td><td><a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCU-eXjZ7Ud0k2wC_14mqdOw" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Elokuba (Qba)</a></td><td>A Manjaro KDE distro.</td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://ps4linux.com/forums/d/334-garuda-linux-ext4-rc1-yakuza" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Garuda</a></td><td>Arch</td><td><a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCU-eXjZ7Ud0k2wC_14mqdOw" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Elokuba (Qba)</a></td><td>Gaming focused distro</td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://ps4linux.com/forums/d/337-xubuntu-2504-final-release" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Xubuntu</a></td><td>Ubuntu</td><td>triki1</td><td>Divided into multiple files</td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://ps4linux.com/forums/d/252-batocera-40-for-ps4-installation-setup-tutorial" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Batocera 40</a></td><td>No clue</td><td>Noob404</td><td>For retrogaming</td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://github.com/Jaguarlinux" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">JaguarLinux</a></td><td>None</td><td>TigerClips1</td><td>A distro made from scratch for the PS4! Still in development, but worth mentioning.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>IF you choose CachyOS (probably the other ones too), remember to use the specified kernel, and also use the bootargs.txt file. <strong>Needs to be in the same folder of the bzImage</strong>.</p><div class="tip custom-block github-alert"><p class="custom-block-title">TIP</p><p>Want to add more distros? Make an issue and your wish shall be granted.</p><p>Want to make your own? <a href="https://ps4linux.com/make-ps4-linux-distro/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Check this out!</a></p></div><h2 id="payloads-kinda-optional" tabindex="-1">Payloads (kinda optional) <a class="header-anchor" href="#payloads-kinda-optional" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Payloads (kinda optional)&quot;">​</a></h2><p>For those who don&#39;t want to open a browser everytime (saves like 15-30 seconds for those sweet top 1% speedruns)</p><p><a href="https://github.com/ps4boot/ps4-linux-payloads" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Download them from here</a>, and extract the one you want in your <code>data/payloads</code> folder. Remember to use the one that is for your Southbridge (you have understood that by now). If it doesn&#39;t have any particularly append, it&#39;s for both Aeolia and Belize.</p>',19)])])}const m=e(l,[["render",i]]);export{c as __pageData,m as default};
